		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>I highly recommend that you add NO SURRENDER SOLDIER (Merit Press, 2014) by Christine Kohler.      NO SURRENDER SOLDIER is set on Guam and all the characters are Chamorro, Japanese, or mixed-race Guamanians. This multi-cultural story is rich in diverse ethnic culture in a U.S. territory few Americans know much about.   It is a beautifully written story about a unique and important subject.</p>
<p>Gayle Rosengren</p>
		</div>

