		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Please consider adding Cry of the Sea by D. G. Driver to your list of diverse books. It is a new YA novel about an American Indian teen who discovers mermaids washed up on a beach during an oil spill. There have been many posts over the past few weeks on the WeNeedDiverseBooks campaign about how people want to see diverse characters in fantasy and science fictions books.  This is one of them.  Published by Fire and Ice in February, 2014.</p>
		</div>

