		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>I would love for you to include my Lola stories featuring book-loving Lola and her family (who just happen to be African American). They are published by Charlesbridge who have been publishing thoughtful, careful, beautiful, inclusive books for many years. As one of your earlier commentators said, we must not forget to support smaller, independent publishers who do such good work. It&#8217;s hard to select from Charlesbridge&#8217;s list, but my favourite is Global Babies and Global Girls Babies. Readers might also be interested in: Children of Native America Today (I like the emphasis on &#8216;today&#8217;). <a href="http://www.charlesbridge.com/catalog.cfm?CatPos=209" rel="nofollow">http://www.charlesbridge.com/catalog.cfm?CatPos=209</a> or <a href="http://www.charlesbridge.com/contributorinfo.cfm?ContribID=260" rel="nofollow">http://www.charlesbridge.com/contributorinfo.cfm?ContribID=260</a></p>
