		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Thank you for expanding the list. I agree with including Laura Resau&#8217;s books. They are rich in culture and lush in setting descriptions. I would humbly like to add my picture book, JALAPENO BAGELS, beautifully illustrated by Robert Casilla, (Atheneum) about a boy with a Mexican mother and Jewish father who has to decide what to bring to school for International Day that represents his culture. He goes to his parents&#8217; bakery and chooses jalapeño bagels because they represent that he is multicultural. The book includes Spanish and Yiddish words, and recipes for baked goods. Thank you for continuing this discussion and shining a light on books that appeal to a wider range of America&#8217;s population mix.</p>
		</div>

