		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>What a lovely conversation this is!  I recognize so many wonderful titles I have read and handled over the years (just retired from media work at Lincoln Public Schools after 38 yrs) and also recognize many names of wonderful people engaged in promoting diverse literature.<br />
I&#8217;ve just read a title called &#8216;Eggplant Alley&#8217; by David Cataneo. Though is mainly a story of an Italian-American family&#8230; the cast of multi-cultural characters deal with bigotry, the changing faces of a neighborhood, conflicted feelings about the Vietnam War, and a boy&#8217;s coming of age and discovering that the world is not necessarily like his family has taught him it is.</p>
